if the client can't send alt lyrics - first confirm what they actually want taken out (preferably a lyric pdf with naughty words highlighted if there's a lot going on)

if there aren't any words in the session you can fly in that make sense, precisely chop out (don't forget any doubles/harms/printed verbs, doublers, or parallels)
and get creative with blurring over that gap - delay throws, reverb toss, stuttering the previous/next word, reverse reverb into it, all of the above who cares as long as it sounds dope

@JustinLeu is right on. 

Sometimes getting fresh ears is the ticket. I sent a mix to @BatMeckley today cause I know he doesn’t respect anybody or anything, and he came back all compliments and two very actionable notes. 

Sometimes someone just sitting in the room with you while you work is enough to get you outta your head.

@Edward Rivera Might need to buy tupe.

@JustinLeu maybe saturn is the solution here!

@Nick Stetina I have never used Kelvin! will look into it.

The Little Radiator is doing something cool for me right now and also messing with just the tape sat on EchoBoy. But Not totally sold. It's gonna be a huge part of the drum sound on these mixes

if you happen to have a MWTM subscription Eddie Kramer discusses exactly this as being the necessary process when they had to commit everything to 4 tracks (i think) forJimi Hendrix-  are you experienced . Its an inspiring listen to hear what they achoeved that way..
i know you mention the pie comp a lot, kramer Loves that comp lol, he talks about smashing the pianos and guitars with it.

@cian riordan coincidentally i was just watching st,Vincent’s production process video on reverb over the last few days and wondered how much of what she does ....with the verbs and delays comes baked in to you ...and if so how you approached it as a mixer. I wondered if it sort of tied your hands a bit for possible decisions...but from your post above about baking it in early  ....i guess it suits just fine. V Dope
